LAGOS  – Comptroller Festus Okun, Customs Area Controller of Port Terminal Multiservice Limited (PTML), Command of Nigeria Customs Service(NCS ),has charged newly promoted officers to continually uphold tenets of integrity and redouble their dedication to service. Okun made the call while administering the decoration of promoted officers with their new ranks. He urged them to justify the confidence reposed in them by the management of the service and see their promotions as call to higher responsibilities. While congratulating the newly elevated officers, he advised them not to see their new rank as a bed of roses, but as a challenge to work more in the interest of the nation in terms of national economic and security sustenance. He described customs job as a knowledge-based activity, advised the officers to always refresh their knowledge about the service, not only for promotion examination purposes, but also for their day-to- day official functions. “I am happy to be part of your excelling moments in your service history and will want to urge you to contribute more to the service by uphold tenets of integrity at all times. “As your area controller, I appreciate your efforts in the past and believe that Nigeria deserve more. I hereby urge you all to redouble in the areas of maximum revenue collection, suppression of smuggling, trade facilitation and discharging all policies of the Federal Government as directed. “The Comptroller General of Customs, Col Hameed Ibrahim Ali(Rtd), always look forward to the patriotic and uncompromising discharge of our official activities. Let’s use our offices to prevent revenue loss, duty evasion, smuggling and other vices under our official purview,” the CAC said. POLL Comptroller Okun was assisted by other senior officers of the rank of Deputy Comptroller of Customs in the decoration exercise.